# Static brand assets and related files

Full detail lives in-repo—keep rules and files aligned:

## Markdown table of contents (repo-wide)

- Any **multi-section** Markdown file in the repository (two or more `##` headings) must include **`## Table of contents`** right after the title/intro block, linking to **each `##` section**. Nested `###` links are optional. Use **GitHub-style fragment IDs**: lowercase, spaces to `-`, punctuation removed (hover a rendered heading on GitHub to copy the fragment).
- **Exempt:** [`CHANGELOG.md`](../../CHANGELOG.md) — maintained by the release script and contains duplicate-heading examples inside fenced blocks. **One-section stubs** with at most one body `##` after the title do not require a TOC.
- [`docs/README.md`](../../docs/README.md) is the documentation index; update it when adding top-level guides under `docs/`.

**Reference guides**

- [`docs/asset-naming.md`](../../docs/asset-naming.md) — kebab-case filenames; spell out product names (not `gtmt`-style abbreviations in shipped names); role suffixes `-mark`, `-wordmark`, **`-lockup-horizontal` / `-lockup-stacked`** (orientation required; no bare `-lockup`), `-icon`, `-og`; optional `…-lockup-horizontal-badge` when both open (knockout) and enclosed (pill/chip) lockups ship; **`src/brand/<project-slug>/`** per product (same slug style as favicons), not one umbrella folder for every mark.
- [`src/brand/README.md`](../../src/brand/README.md) — canonical spec for `src/brand/`: layout, **SVG** vs **PNG RGBA**, dimensions, OG, greyscale filter `id` rules. **Greyscale:** prefer CSS when possible; add `…-mark-greyscale.svg` / `…-lockup-horizontal-greyscale.svg` / `…-lockup-stacked-greyscale.svg` only when a committed asset is required. Docs hub: [`docs/README.md`](../../docs/README.md#brand-assets-marks-and-lockups). Package subpath `./brand/<project-slug>/*`.
- [`src/favicons/README.md`](../../src/favicons/README.md) — favicon bundle layout, import path, recommended files, PWA sizes.
- [`src/banners/README.md`](../../src/banners/README.md) — place banners in `src/banners/<project-slug>/`; use `-banner` role with explicit variants (`-mobile`, `-desktop`, `-light`, `-dark`) and platform suffixes (`-x`, `-linkedin-company`, `-facebook-page`, etc.); prefer WebP for raster delivery.

## When editing brand assets, favicons, or `package.json`

- After renaming or adding files under `src/brand/`, update **`exports`** and the **`build`** copy step if the folder is new or renamed.
- After adding banner files under `src/banners/<project-slug>/`, run a full **`build`** so `dist/banners/` updates (`./banners/*` export; no new `exports` row per project).
- Keep one favicon bundle per project under `src/favicons/<project-slug>/` and preserve standard filenames (`favicon.svg`, `favicon.ico`, `apple-touch-icon.png`, `icon-192.png`, `icon-512.png` when available).
- Keep one banner set per project under `src/banners/<project-slug>/` and use explicit suffixes such as `-banner-mobile`, `-banner-desktop`, `-banner-light`, `-banner-dark`.
- For social media exports, use platform-specific filenames (`-banner-x`, `-banner-linkedin-company`, `-banner-facebook-page`, `-banner-mastodon`, `-banner-instagram-story`, `-banner-instagram-post-4x5`) instead of generic names.
- **Playground (same PR, mandatory):** Any **new or renamed** asset under **`src/brand/`**, **`src/favicons/`**, or **`src/banners/`** that ships to **`dist/`** must appear in **`playground/`** before merge—usually via the **Brand** / **Banners** / **Favicons** tabs after extending **`playground/src/distAssetGlobs.ts`** if needed, or a **labeled preview** in **`playground/src/App.tsx`**. Aligns with the always-applied **`organization-assets-package.mdc`** playground section.
- If conventions in `docs/*.md` or colocated `src/*/README.md` files change, update this rule file in the same PR so Cursor stays aligned.
- Update `CHANGELOG.md` `[Unreleased]` section when adding or renaming assets.

## Examples

- Prefer `grow-the-music-tree-mark.png` over `gtmt.png`.
- Prefer `audiometa-lockup-horizontal.svg` (or `…-lockup-stacked.svg`) with explicit **`-mark`** / **`-wordmark`** roles over vague compound filenames for identity artwork.
- Prefer `@themusictree/brand/brand/audiometa/audiometa-mark.png` over legacy umbrella paths or `brand/cv/...`.
- Prefer `grow-the-music-tree-banner-mobile.webp` over `hero-mobile-final.webp`.
